00:41:15,449 --> 00:41:17,429
And then DJ Earbud comes on.

992
00:41:17,469 --> 00:41:18,289
Doot-de-doot-de-doot.

993
00:41:19,896 --> 00:41:21,116
for an hour, and you're like, oh, anyway.

994
00:41:21,436 --> 00:41:23,497
So that doesn't usually happen in the office.

995
00:41:24,157 --> 00:41:26,398
But sometimes, you know, offices can be really noisy.

996
00:41:26,458 --> 00:41:29,679
In our place, we put up sound padding around

997
00:41:29,699 --> 00:41:31,680
because there was echo that was a little irritating.

998
00:41:31,700 --> 00:41:33,961
We put the sound padding, and it was better.

999
00:41:34,161 --> 00:41:35,282
The communication was a little clearer.

1000
00:41:36,302 --> 00:41:37,542
But then there's other ones, interruptions.

1001
00:41:37,603 --> 00:41:39,623
People come in and bug in you all the time.

1002
00:41:39,863 --> 00:41:41,924
A lot of places have developed kind of an informal code

1003
00:41:41,944 --> 00:41:43,885
of, hey, if I've got headphones on, don't bother me.

1004
00:41:44,105 --> 00:41:45,265
I'm busy right now, right?

1005
00:41:47,008 --> 00:41:48,128
Another one is lying.

1006
00:41:49,188 --> 00:41:51,229
Lying is a kind of noise on information.

1007
00:41:51,689 --> 00:41:53,369
Someone's delivering information,

1008
00:41:53,409 --> 00:41:54,830
but it's not the right information.

1009
00:41:54,870 --> 00:41:55,710
